Package: fsuite
Architecture: all
Depends: ${misc:Depends}, bash (>= 4.0), coreutils, findutils, perl
Recommends: tree, ripgrep, fd-find, python3, sqlite3
Description: Filesystem reconnaissance toolkit for humans and AI agents
 fsuite provides six composable CLI tools that turn filesystem
 exploration into a clean, scriptable, agent-friendly pipeline:
 .
  * fsearch - Find files by name, extension, or glob pattern
  * fcontent - Search inside files for text (powered by ripgrep)
  * ftree - Visualize directory structure with smart defaults and recon mode
  * fmap - Extract structural skeleton of code files (code cartography)
  * fread - Read files with budgets, context windows, and diff-aware ranges
  * fmetrics - Analyze local telemetry and predict runtime
 .
 The reconnaissance tools output in multiple formats (pretty, paths,
 JSON) for both human and programmatic consumption. Includes telemetry
 analytics via fmetrics for performance tracking.
